nodes.bodyText:
Do we need to execute the current logic (logging) if the user has specified a custom function?
Instead of making this nilable shall we just have the functions and assign as the default implementation the current logic that logs?
Given that delivery failure can happen due to three reasons, we can add maybe add another FailureReason parameter to quickly figure out what went wrong, and in the default case log the appropriate log.
const FAILURE_REASON_SUBSCRIPTION_GONE = "SUBSCRIPTION_GONE";
const FAILURE_REASON_FAILURE_STATUS_CODE = "FAILURE_STATUS_CODE";
const FAILURE_REASON_DELIVERY_FAILURE = "DELIVERY_FAILURE";

type FailureReason FAILURE_REASON_SUBSCRIPTION_GONE|FAILURE_REASON_FAILURE_STATUS_CODE|FAILURE_REASON_DELIVERY_FAILURE;

function (string callback, string topic, WebSubContent content, http:Response|error response, FailureReason reason) onDeliveryFailureFunction = defaultOnDeliveryFailureFunction;
This way we can avoid having to use the type test per delivery.

